# Compiled binary (built with `go build ./cmd/thought`)
/thought
# Stable build output linked onto PATH (~/.local/bin/thought -> bin/thought); see Makefile
/bin/
# Other built cmd binaries (go build ./cmd/<x>) that must never be committed
/bench
/costest
/trprobe
/speedbench
# Go test/build artifacts
*.test
*.out

# Benchmark / trace-probe RUN OUTPUTS under runs/ — regenerated artifacts, never source.
# Ignore the WHOLE dir (the old per-glob list missed *.console, *.txt, *.err, etc.).
# (Pin a curated baseline by force-adding it: `git add -f runs/<name>`.)
/runs/
# Substrate-segregated registry STATE (mutable, campaign-minted; never source — stays on
# disk + in history, but the campaign churns it, so it must not be tracked).
/data/registry-*/
